    <p>Instela Maestros are self employed and are solely responsible for the quality and outcome of the work they do. Instela acts as an agent to introduce the Parties and disclaims any liability in the Services that are provided. As a Instela Maestro you are responsible for your own Tax affairs.</p>

    <h3>Trust</h3>

    <p>Instela takes reasonable steps to On-Board Maestros who are experienced in the Services they provide. We check ID, proof of address and right to work and take reasonable steps to determine experience, which may include reference checking. The Parties may review each other at the end of a Job and these reviews may be available to provide assurance. Instela does not accept liability on the suitability of the Maestro to do Jobs or the quality of the outcome and the Parties must determine for themselves if they want to engage.</p>

    <h3>Doing Jobs</h3>

    <p>As a Instela Customer you can create a Job. The Job will include a description, location and a price that is predetermined by Instela, either per hour or per job. You may also upload photographs relating to the Job and in so doing you agree not to submit photographs that are likely to offend.</p>

    <p>Instela will assign a Maestro to the Job and the Maestro will normally be available within one hour. We provide an estimate of the arrival time at the time of Posting the job; this time is indicative and may vary.</p>

    <h3>Cancellation Policy</h3>

    <p>You may cancel a Job anytime, after the given period displayed on the applications or website the minimum fee will be charged, if cancelled within grace period displayed no fee will be due. If our professionals arrive at the job location and are unable to contact you or gain access to the job location they will message and attempt to contact you for 10 mins, after which you will be charged the minimum fee and the job will be cancelled.</p>

    <h3>Card Pre-Authorisation</h3>

    <p>When a Customer Posts a Job we may pre-authorise payment of a minimum of the first hour of the Job on the payment card added to the app. A Job will only be Posted when the pre-authorisation is successfully received. This pre-authorisation will be released if the Job is cancelled or at the time of final payment.</p>

    <p>We reserve the right to take the pre-authorisation amount in the event the payment for a job is not fully collected and you accept our right to do this.</p>

    <h3>Maestro – Responding to Jobs</h3>

    <p>As a Instela Maestro you will be assigned Jobs that have been Posted by Customers when you are online and available for work. You must accept or reject a Job within 5 minutes or the Job may be assigned to another Maestro.</p>

    <p>If you continually reject Jobs after going online we may cancel your registration.</p>

    <p>You warrant that in accepting a Job you will complete the Job as specified, to the standards and timescales agreed with the Customer.</p>

    <h3>Pricing</h3>

    <p>A Job is Posted at a pre-determined price, which may be per hour or per Job. The price includes Instela’s commission, which is a percentage of the price of the Job and may vary from time to time at Instela’s sole discretion. For Jobs that have a per hour price the first hour will be charged in full regardless of the time spent by the Maestro in doing the Job. Subsequent hours after the first hour will be charged per minute. Instela reserves the right to change prices at any time.</p>

    <h3>Expenses</h3>

    <p>If during a Job a Maestro incurs additional expenses directly relating to a Job, for example a handyman purchasing an item to complete a plumbing job, the Maestro will ask the Customer to pay for such expenses in cash on the production of a valid receipt. This policy however does not apply to cleaning products. Maestros are expected to supply all their cleaning products. Customers however are expected to supply the cleaning Maestros with a mop and vacuum cleaner.</p>

    <h3>Payment</h3>

    <p>When a Job is completed Instela calculates the final amount to be paid, including applicable discounts. The Customer may release payment or Instela may take payment.</p>

    <p>The Customer agrees to hold sufficient funds in their account to pay the final amount as it becomes due and will not Post a Job unless they can pay for it. We may, at our sole discretion, not allow a Customer to Post a Job if we are outstanding the payment for a prior Job.</p>

    <p>Instela does not accept cash payments. All Jobs are Posted using a valid payment card and final payment is taken from the card once the Job is completed. Instela reserves the right not to accept certain payment cards including, but not limited to, pre-payment cards.</p>

    <p>Instela Maestros are paid up to 4 working days after the Customer has paid for the Job, direct into a nominated bank account.</p>

    <h3>Tax</h3>

    <p>As a Maestro, you agree that you are responsible for your own accounting and tax affairs and that you will hold Instela entirely harmless from any claims from HMRC or any other statutory body.</p>

