    <p>Instela does not directly hold payment card information.</p>

    <p>Instela will be responsible for paying the fees charged by the Payment Services.</p>

    <h3>Disputes and Dispute Resolution</h3>

    <p>If the Customer is not satisfied that the Maestro has completed the Job to the performance and/or quality the Customer may reasonably expect, the Parties may enter into a Dispute. The Parties may also enter into a Dispute if the Maestro is not satisfied the Customer has correctly described the Job to be done. The parties may only enter a Dispute within 14 days of the Job completion date. In the event of a Dispute the Parties hereby agree to negotiate a settlement in good faith and hereby recognise that the responsibility for reaching a mutually agreed settlement lies between them.</p>

    <p>If the Parties cannot reach resolution between themselves it will be escalated to Instela and we will offer a recommendation for settlement of the Dispute. Instela will request information to be provided by both Maestro and Customer and you agree to provide information that may be reasonably available to support Instela in proposing a resolution. The Parties are under no obligation to accept any recommendation from Instela, which is not binding.</p>

    <p>In its decision Instela may impose a solution on the Parties, which may include a solution for final payment. In so doing the Parties accept that Instela may impose such a solution. Should either Party decide to take further action beyond Instela’s final decision Instela will provide information to a court or other body of competent jurisdiction and will absorb reasonable expenses in so doing. In no event will Instela incur costs higher than the original agreed price of the Job.</p>

    <p>Instela reserves the right, at our sole discretion, to terminate the account of a User who it deems is entering into an excessive number of Disputes.</p>

    <h3>Loss or Damage</h3>

    <p>If the Customer suffers loss or damage to their property and attributes the loss or damage to a Maestro, in the first instance the Parties should try to resolve between themselves, which Instela may facilitate. Instela will initiate a claims procedure if the loss or damage is reported to us and may take further action including reporting the matter to the police.</p>

    <p>The absolute limit on any damage claim that we accept on behalf of the Maestro is £50.</p>

    <h3>Recommendations and Reviews</h3>

    <p>Customers and Maestros are encouraged to offer reviews for each other each time a Job is completed. You agree to provide a prompt review that is true and fully reflects your experience with the Customer or Maestro with who you have engaged.</p>

